Quick start

Source: vignettes/main_function.Rmd
main_function.Rmd
library(cardinalR)
library(langevitour)
rotations_4d <- list(
cluster1 = list(
  list(plane = c(1, 2), angle = 60), # Rotation in the (1, 2) plane
  list(plane = c(3, 4), angle = 90)  # Rotation in the (3, 4) plane
  ),
cluster2 = list(
  list(plane = c(1, 3), angle = 30) # Rotation in the (1, 3) plane
  ),
cluster3 = list(
  list(plane = c(2, 4), angle = 45) # Rotation in the (2, 4) plane
  )
)

dim4_weights <- list(
cluster1 = c(1.0, 1.0, 1,0, 1,0),
cluster2 = c(1.0, 1.0, 1,0, 0.3),
cluster3 = c(1.0, 1.0, 1,0, 0.3)
)

clust_data <- gen_multicluster(n = c(200, 300, 500), p = 4, k = 3,
loc = matrix(c(
  0, 0, 0, 0,
  4, 6, 0, 0,
  3, 4, 5, 6
), nrow = 4, byrow = TRUE),
dim_weights = dim4_weights,
scale = c(3, 1, 6),
shape = c("gaussian", "bluntedcorn", "unifcube"),
rotation = rotations_4d,
is_bkg = FALSE)

#> âœ” Data generation completed successfully! ðŸŽ‰

langevitour(clust_data |> dplyr::select(-cluster), 
            pointSize = 2, group = clust_data$cluster)
